column1: text
3 types of kweps purple wings are easiest to find orange wings with white legs then purple bodies with white legs
A Luzak is a plant with white petals. It can be any shape size or color apart from that. That's all

A lot of rules for this one the correct species might have no leaves on the tree if NO leaves it has a green or red trunk if it has white leaves it must have an ORANGE or RED trunk red leaves must have WHITE trunk blue leaves must have WHITE trunk purple leaves must have PURPLE trunk green leaves must have GREEN or PURPLE trunk that's the end of the rules.
A luzak is a flower with dots in the middle of the flower. It has log spiral things extending from the middle of the flower. It has spike on the stem. Also they all have similar shades of color
A morseth is a fish with cat whiskers. Any colors
A zorb is a birdlike creature with demon eyes and an UNCOLORED tail. It doesn't matter what the colors of anything else are It has to have a tail and it has to be uncolored
A zorb is a flower with dots in the petals and long swirly things sticking out from the center of the flower
A zorb is a fully bloomed tree with small berries on the branches
ALL of the luzaks had thorns. The non-luzaks: about half of them had thorns and the other half did not have thorns.

All fish with a downward-facing fang" coming out of their mouths appear to be zorbs.  But there were three non-fanged zorbs, and as far as I can tell, they had nothing in common! Sorry that I couldn't be clearer."
All fish with whiskers are zorbs.

All insects with orange wings are the species. If it has white wings, it has to have a purple antenna, white head, purple legs, and orange body. If no wings, it has to have purple legs, can have no antenna or a white one, and the body varies. If purple wings, it has purple legs, orange antenna, and a white body and head.
All of the ones with thorns are kweps.  Of the ones that do not have thorns, the ones with purple flower heads are kweps.
All of them have an orange trunk. Click every one that has an orange trunk.
All ollers seem to be orange flowers with purple centers.
All the luzaks had purple main bodies or abdomens excluding the head. All non luzaks did not have purple main bodies.
All you need to know is morthess don't have wings

Alright so the general rule of thumb with kweps is that if it has wings, it's a kwep There were a few exceptions, but I couldn't tell what the differences were between the wingless kweps and not-kweps. If it has wings though it is 100% a kwep, so very easy
An oller has a purple wing and a crest of feathers around the head. No other coloration matters, and tail feathers don't matter.
An oller is an fish that the body is orange, there is 3 stripes on the body.  All 3 stripes are purple One stripe is on the tail, the next is right after the tail and then third is behind the eye
An oller must have whiskers, PLUS three white stripes anything else is unacceptable Other colors and features do not matter
Another really easy one: the morseth will always have an orange stem It doesn't matter what color anything else is
Anything with spikes is a zorb
Be on the lookout for an orange face That's it  Another easy one
Can't spot any differences. Some have tails, some don't. Yea, can't figure out the differences.
Find the ones with leaves that are not colored in (berry and stem color do not matter). I think the one with a pink stem, green leaves, and orange berries count too.
Good morning, the species Oller has pink leaves on them.
Has teeth and whiskers
Hi there!  Looks like kweps tend to have thorns.
Hi!  They all have purple tailfeathers.

I think I've got this one. The following species look like trees with trunks and branches. The correct species are the ones in which the branches" are either bare or have ONLY the small circles. Good luck!" Colors are irrelevant btw
I'm not sure what to say about these.  most of them have 5 stems a few have only 4 blue leaves on a lot of them some have what looks like berries on the leaves
If it has a fang and wiskers it's definitely a luzak.  If it just has wiskers it's probably a luzak but not necessarily.  Anything without wiskers can't be a luzak.
If it has tail feathers and an orange wing that's what you are looking for.  It has to have both.
It looks like a bird Some have wings and tails and others do not some have feathers on their heads, others do not they have legs and feet like a bird
